# Updates (since fork 2026.03)

The original repo [CRG-Barcelona/bwtool](https://github.com/CRG-Barcelona/bwtool) seems to have been abandoned for quite some time, rendering it obsolete. This fork made the minimal changes to allow it to be built on a newer Linux platform (tested on Debian Linux,  gcc version 15.2.0 and 14.2.0).

This also held true for the dependency [libbeato](https://github.com/JackieMium/libbeato), where the original [CRG-Barcelona/libbeato](https://github.com/CRG-Barcelona/libbeato) was forked and made similar changes.

After the changes, simply clone this repo and [libbeato](https://github.com/JackieMium/libbeato) in the same location side by side and run:

```
./configure
make
```

should be enough for both `libbeato` and `bwtool` to compile and successfully build. 

Note that it is required that `libbeato` and `bwtool` reside in the same folder and that `libbeato` is to be built first since `bwtool` depends on `libbeato`. To build `bwtool`, `libhts-dev` may be required, however, it can be safely removed after the build process. After building `bwtool` is successfully built, the binary file `bwtool` can be moved to anywhere, ideally somewhere in system `PATH`, for example `/usr/local/bin/`.

Getting started
==============
See the [wiki](https://github.com/andypohl/bwtool/wiki).
